            <tr><td>GVK Rao Committee</td><td>1985</td><td>District as planning unit; coined "grass without roots" for PRIs</td></tr>
            <tr><td>1st ARC</td><td>1966</td><td>Morarji Desai → K. Hanumanthaiah; 537 recommendations; 20 reports</td></tr>
            <tr><td>2nd ARC</td><td>2005</td><td>Veerappa Moily; 15 reports; e-governance, ethics, Lokayukta in every state</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="gk-note">
      <strong>Common exam trap:</strong> "Dharam Vira Commission 1969" is a widely circulated error — <strong>there is no such commission</strong>. Dharam Vira chaired the National Police Commission constituted in <strong>November 1977</strong>. Also: Rajamannar Committee was set up by Tamil Nadu state government (not Central govt) — the only state-constituted committee on this list. All others were Central Government committees.
    </div>

